         <abstract>
            <p>Although it's easy to say total water management (TWM), the multifaceted concept is difficult to explain. One researcher found 35 ways TWM can be implemented, but his list boiled down to practical items such as coordinating water and wastewater; federal, state, and local actions; and the work of engineers and financial managers. No matter how you cut it, there are numerous ways to look at TWM.</p>
